|update = Death Changes
|change = Items lost on death will now be in your gravestone. They cost coins to reclaim and in PVP, the gravestone is visible and claimable freely to the player killer.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 22 May 2015
|update = Temporary Death Mechanic Changes
|change = Items dropped on death now remain on the floor for 60 minutes before disappearing. In PVP, they are only visible to the player killer for one minute and everyone else for the following 59 minutes.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 13 February 2015
|update = Change to Items Lost on Death
|change = Items dropped on death are now invisible to other players outside of PVP.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 16 October 2014
|update = Corporeal Beast
|change = Items dropped on death were changed to stay on the floor for 30 minutes before disappearing, being visible only to the player who died for one minute. In PVP, they are only visible to the player killer for one minute.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 9 October 2014
|update = New Bounty Hunter Rewards
|change = Temporary changes to death mechanics were reverted; items would again appear to everyone immediately and disappear in two minutes.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 29 September 2014
|update = Temporary Changes to Death Mechanics (29 September 2014)
|change = Items dropped on death were changed to stay on the floor for 30 minutes before disappearing, being visible only to the player who died for one minute. This change did not affect PVP.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 4 September 2014
|update = Player Owned House Menageries
|change = Temporary changes to death mechanics were reverted; items would again appear to everyone immediately and disappear in two minutes.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 20 August 2014
|update = Temporary Changes to Death Mechanics (29 September 2014)
|change = Items dropped on death were changed to stay on the floor for 30 minutes before disappearing, being visible only to the player who died for one minute. This change did not affect PVP.
}}
{{Subject changes
